The current change is a reference for only the USSD over CDMA-IMS scenario (not UT/Supplementary Services). Since USSD is not supported over ImsPhone (ImsPhoneMmiCode) anyways, this change appears to be CS-only.

The change is an reference (using USSD as an example) on how all MMI codes - supplementary service (UT), and USSD - can be handled over CDMA-IMS scenarios. For the full CDMA-IMS functionality, more refactoring will be required in AOSP to route the MMI codes over ImsPhone -> ImsPhoneMmiCode

